comment._content: Lockheed Model 18-56 Lodestar NC2333 was impressed by the USAAF as C-56 41-19729 4-2-41, later became N61M, and is now at the Travis Air Museum. [http://www.flickr.com/photos/93373926@N04/8636217176/in/photostream/] via rods fotos. However two listings of US civil registrations have Lockheed 14-N Super Electra c/n 1417 also with the registration NC2333, which became RAF AX681. Maybe they gave the reg NC2333 to the 14 first, then when that aircraft went to the RAF the reg was recycled and applied to the Lodestar? Below are photos of Model 14 NC2333 on SDASM's Flickr page. [http://www.flickr.com/photos/sdasmarchives/4589887625/] [http://www.flickr.com/photos/sdasmarchives/4589887649/in/photostream/]
